This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as entity linking and fine-grained entity typing, which are typically categorized under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces new methods for integrating hierarchical information, which involves machine learning techniques and optimization, making it relevant to subfields such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves working with large datasets and ontologies, which could fall under subfields such as information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
